## Adding Cross-Cutting Impacts

To declare impact on additional focus groups:

1. **Interactive Method:** Run `/wgsd declare-impact {{CONCEPT_SLUG}}`
2. **Manual Method:** Add entries to the `impacts:` array in YAML frontmatter

### Impact Type Reference

| Type | Description | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `primary-owner` | This FG owns the concept | The originating focus group |
| `breaking-change` | API/behavior breaking changes | Endpoint signature changes |
| `api-change` | Non-breaking API modifications | New optional parameters |
| `documentation` | Docs must be updated | API reference changes |
| `integration` | Integration touchpoints affected | Auth flow changes |
| `testing` | Test suite modifications needed | New test scenarios |
| `behavior` | Behavior changes (non-breaking) | Default value changes |
| `security` | Security implications | Token handling, permissions |
| `performance` | Performance considerations | Query optimization needs |

### Priority Reference

| Priority | SLA | Description |
|----------|-----|-------------|
| P0 | 4h | Critical - blocks other work |
| P1 | 24h | High - affects current sprint |
| P2 | 72h | Medium - planned work impact |
| P3 | 7d | Low - nice to know |

